rious technologies as they become relevant In addition to excellent written and verbal communication skills, the ideal candidate will also have: 1-2 years experience developing Blockchain applications A BS or MS in a related field or equivalent experience Hands-on experience writing and deploying smart contracts with Ethereum Strong software engineering background; will be participating in all aspects of the software development lifecycle Experience with blockchain protocols, sidechains, and scaling technologies Perks and Compensation For this role we are considering both full-time and contract arrangements depending on candidate preferences and needs. Our preference is full time. For full-time employees, we offer professional development opportunities through various course materials and on-the-job training. Flexible work hours. Friendly, accepting workplace of people who like to roll up their sleeves and make things. Access to deep knowledge of all facets of cryptocurrency. Competitive salary. Profit sharing and equity in spun-off companies based on our technology portfolio. Paid Holidays, Vacation and Health insurance after 3 months. ORCA or Puget Sound Transit card for mass transit commuters. Equal Opportunity Employer. We actively seek to build a diverse workplace. Please send a resume and short introduction letter to billy@hornofthemoon.com. ", 
